<h1 class="title toc-ignore">Using <code>gadmVN</code></h1>
<h4 class="author"><em>Marc Choisy</em></h4>
<h4 class="date"><em>2017-05-15</em></h4>



<p>This package contains the polygons of Vietnam and its provinces at different points in time since 1979, reflecting the changes in the administrative divisions along the history of Vietnam.</p>
<div id="installation-and-loading" class="section level2">
<h2>Installation and loading</h2>
<p>You can install <code>gadmVN</code> from GitHub with:</p>
<div class="sourceCode"><pre class="sourceCode r"><code class="sourceCode r">&gt;<span class="st"> </span><span class="co"># install.packages(&quot;devtools&quot;)</span>
<span class="er">&gt;</span><span class="st"> </span>devtools::<span class="kw">install_github</span>(<span class="st">&quot;choisy/gadmVN&quot;</span>, <span class="dt">build_vignettes =</span> <span class="ot">TRUE</span>)</code></pre></div>
<p>Once installed, you can load the package:</p>
<div class="sourceCode"><pre class="sourceCode r"><code class="sourceCode r">&gt;<span class="st"> </span><span class="kw">library</span>(gadmVN)</code></pre></div>
</div>
<div id="usage-examples" class="section level2">
<h2>Usage examples</h2>
<p><code>SpatialPolygonsDataFrame</code> can be retrieved thanks to the <code>gadm</code> function. The first argument is the date at which we want the map (either a text in the “YYYY-MM-DD” format or a 4-digit numeric format of the year). The second argument specifies the level we are interested in (either “provinces” or “country”), the third argument is the level of resolution we want (either “low” or “high”) and the last argument tells whether we want the province of Ha Noi and Ha Son Binh to be merged. This latter argument makes a difference only for date before 1992-01-01.</p>
<p>The map of the provinces in 1992</p>
<div class="sourceCode"><pre class="sourceCode r"><code class="sourceCode r">&gt;<span class="st"> </span>pr &lt;-<span class="st"> </span><span class="kw">gadm</span>(<span class="dv">1992</span>)</code></pre></div>
<p>Maping 4 categories of provinces according to latitude:</p>
<div class="sourceCode"><pre class="sourceCode r"><code class="sourceCode r">&gt;<span class="st"> </span>latitudes &lt;-<span class="st"> </span><span class="kw">coordinates</span>(pr)[, <span class="dv">2</span>]
&gt;<span class="st"> </span>breaks &lt;-<span class="st"> </span><span class="kw">seq</span>(<span class="kw">min</span>(latitudes), <span class="kw">max</span>(latitudes), <span class="dt">le =</span> <span class="dv">5</span>)
&gt;<span class="st"> </span>palette &lt;-<span class="st"> </span><span class="kw">c</span>(<span class="st">&quot;red&quot;</span>, <span class="st">&quot;blue&quot;</span>, <span class="st">&quot;green&quot;</span>, <span class="st">&quot;orange&quot;</span>)
&gt;<span class="st"> </span>colors &lt;-<span class="st"> </span>palette[<span class="kw">as.numeric</span>(<span class="kw">cut</span>(latitudes, breaks, <span class="dt">include =</span> <span class="ot">TRUE</span>))]
&gt;<span class="st"> </span><span class="kw">plot</span>(pr, <span class="dt">col =</span> colors)</code></pre></div>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="407.736" style="display: block; margin: auto;" /></p>
